==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[half]]-[[truth]]}}

# A [[deceptive]] [[statement]], especially one that is only [[partly]] true, is [[incomplete]], or otherwise [[misrepresent]]s reality.

===Usage notes===
Half-truths may use various tools, including statistics, unexpected meanings of words, facts taken out of context, or even non-standard punctuation to corrupt the meaning conveyed by an otherwise true statement. For more information, see Wikipedia's article "[[w:Lie|Lie]]".

